# YieldManagementWiley

Stochastic Yield Management optimization model implemented in **C++ using IBM ILOG CPLEX Concert API**.

This project is a refactored version of an original OPL (`.mod/.dat`) model, rewritten into a fully programmatic optimization model in modern C++.

---

# Overview

The model solves a multi-period airline yield management problem under uncertain demand scenarios.

The optimization determines:

* number of airplanes,
* ticket pricing strategy,
* sales allocation,
* scenario-dependent pricing decisions,
* seat capacity management across multiple periods.

The implementation uses:

* IBM ILOG CPLEX
* Concert Technology API
* CMake
* C++17

---

# Model Characteristics

## Time Structure

The model contains:

* 3 time periods
* 3 passenger classes:

  * First
  * Business
  * Economy
* 3 pricing options per class
* 3 stochastic demand scenarios

---

# Optimization Features

Implemented constraints include:

* single price selection per class,
* stochastic scenario-based pricing,
* demand limitations,
* cumulative seat capacity tracking,
* global aircraft capacity constraints,
* multi-stage recourse decisions.

The objective maximizes expected profit:

```text
Expected Revenue - Aircraft Cost
```

---

